summary: Okay, so...  I don’t post often for reasons of general internet antisocialness (let’s be honest, the world would be a happier...
body:
Okay, so…  I don’t post often for reasons of general internet antisocialness (let’s be honest, the world would be a happier place if we didn’t always all the time share our opinions).  Only in times of absolute necessity do I grab my megaphone to inform the world of something that MUST be known.

With that out of the way, how come there is no music video of Aziraphale and Crowley backed by the absolute classic “I2I”?

Are you gonna tell me that these two (loveable, amazing) utter morons

are not the subject of this 90s classic?

I mean, come on guys…  How did we miss this?  A song about people not seeing eye to eye on things, but belonging together.  This isn’t just an oversight, it’s a travesty.  The good thing is that someone (read: not me) can rectify this complete injustice by making it happen.  

Thank you for your time and now I retreat back into blissful anonymity.

summary:
Aziraphale: *cry of agony*
Crowley, rushing into the room, wings out, eyes blazing, battle ready: What's happened?! What's...
body:
Aziraphale: *cry of agony*
Crowley, rushing into the room, wings out, eyes blazing, battle ready: What's happened?! What's wrong?!
Aziraphale, solemnly placing a hand over his face, the Great British Bake-Off still playing on the TV: She forgot to butter her tin.
Crowley: *gasp* NO!
Aziraphale: I'm afraid so.
Crowley: Her cake! It's so delicate!
Aziraphale: It'll be nothing but crumbs.
Crowley, looking skyward: Is there no mercy left in this world, then? The girl just wants to go to university, you arrogant sod!

title: Aziraphale + plant headcanons
body:
“Azi being nice to plants” is one approach but I vaguely remember that in the book days, there was a (not universal, but very common) headcanon that Aziraphale is terrible at taking care of living things, if you gave him a goldfish he would probably get caught up in a book and it would die, if you gave him a plant he would kill it… etc

Either neglect or

Crowley: Terrifies his plants but they’re the greenest and healthiest, if not necessarily the happiest

Aziraphale: Kills them with kindness. Probably overwaters them or overfertilises or some shit like that. RIP
